                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-158-off893 t18301209-158-crimeloc895"></join>. -About the 9th of October the prisoner hired a room of mine; I cannot swear when I lost these things, but I know they are mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-158-person1432">
                  ANN 
                  SHARPE
               <interp inst="t18301209-158-person1432" type="surname" value="SHARPE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-158-person1432" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-158-person1432" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutor's wife. The prisoner staid only seven days in our house, and left the room locked up till the Monday following; I got an officer to break it open, and then missed every thing that could be carried away - I have found some things.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-158-person1433">
                  STEPHEN 
                  STEVENS
